    "overview_text": "DRONA NEET 2.0  Class 11th Batch Details \n\n1.⁠We'll cover class 11th  Physics, Chemistry, Botany and Zoology for students preparing for the NEET 2028 examination.\n 2.⁠ ⁠All lectures will be conducted Live Online, and in case you miss a session, recorded Lecture will be available to students on the Mission JEET App/Website. \n3.⁠ ⁠Classes will be scheduled in a structured timetable to ensure systematic NEET preparation. \n4.⁠ ⁠There will be two classes per day, and classes will be conducted 6 days a week. \n5.⁠ ⁠PDF Notes of each class will be uploaded after the lecture on the Mission JEET Application. \n6.⁠ ⁠Daily Practice Problems (DPPs) with Video Solutions by the lecture Faculty will be provided to improve problem-solving ability and conceptual understanding. \n7.⁠ ⁠Chapterwise Practice Sheets / Modules (NEET Level) pdfs will be provided for comprehensive practice. \n8.⁠ ⁠A summary lecture of each chapter will be provided after chapter completion for quick revision and concept clarity. \n9.⁠ ⁠Biweekly scheduled tests will be conducted according to the test planner to monitor your preparation progress. \n10.⁠ ⁠Specialized NEET Pattern Tests will also be conducted to evaluate your preparation level.\n11.⁠ ⁠To support your Board preparation along with NEET, free access to the Prarambh Science Batch will be provided. \n12.⁠ ⁠After completion of the syllabus, dedicated revision classes will be conducted for strong exam preparation. \n13.⁠ ⁠Classes will commence on 3rd June 2026, and the complete syllabus will be covered by 10th Feb 2027. \n14.⁠ ⁠The revision phase will continue until 5th March 2027, followed by tests until 15th March 2027. \n15.⁠ ⁠The entire course will remain accessible to you until the NEET 2028 examination. \n16.⁠ ⁠This batch is non-refundable and non-transferable",

